### 1.2 Self-hosted (loaded onto 3090 Ti, served by `pheno-serve-dev`) — 3 models, dual-role for Qwen3.5-0.8B

| # | Scope tier(s) | Canonical HF repo | params_b | arch | ctx | HF last_modified | recency | disk | vRAM (BF16) |
|---|---|---|---|---:|---|---|---:|---:|
| **T0_drafter + T1_small_task** (dual-role) | `Qwen/Qwen3.5-0.8B` | 0.87 | image-text-to-text | (TBD) | 2026-03-02 | ✓ | ~1.8 GB | 1.8 GB |
| T2_workhorse | `LiquidAI/LFM2.5-8B-A1B` | 8.47 | lfm2_moe (1B-active) | (TBD) | 2026-07-02 | ✓ | ~17 GB | ~17 GB (8.47B × 2) |
| T3_mid_moe | `deepreinforce-ai/Ornith-1.0-9B` | 9.41 | qwen3_5-base MoE | (TBD) | 2026-06-25 | ✓ | ~19 GB | ~19 GB |

**Scope tier strategy (per user 2026-07-04):**

`Qwen/Qwen3.5-0.8B` is the same physical model in two role slots:

- **T0_drafter** — always resident on the 3090 Ti as the EAGLE/MTP draft model for the workhorse models (LFM2.5-8B-A1B, Ornith-1.0-9B). Q4_0 quant ≈ 0.9 GB vRAM. Pinned in vRAM, never swapped out.
- **T1_small_task** — when not drafting for a workhorse run, the same Qwen3.5-0.8B serves small scope tasks directly (lint fixes, docstring polish, single-file edits, naming renames, simple test patches). For these tasks it acts as the "primary" agent, not a draft.

This dual-role reduces total disk and memory pressure (one model, two functions) and gives the drafter model real production work when idle — no wasted capacity.

**Notes on self-hosted:**

- **`Qwen3.5-0.8B`** is `image-text-to-text` pipeline_tag, **not** `text-generation`. Many open-source engines expect the text-only variant; if `Qwen3.5-0.8B` doesn't run cleanly under SGLang's text path, fall back to the closest text-only sibling (TBD).
- **`LiquidAI/LFM2.5-8B-A1B`** uses `hf_implementation: lfm2_moe` — needs an LFM2-MOE-aware backend. SGLang 0.5.2 + vLLM 0.20.0 may need a custom integration; if not, fall back to the text-only `LiquidAI/LFM2.5-8B` (non-MoE) variant if it exists.
- **`Ornith-1.0-9B`** is officially tagged `qwen3_5` — it's a Qwen3.5-family model. The MTP-trained derivative `protoLabsAI/Ornith-1.0-9B-MTP-GGUF` exists for the spec-dec zoo eval.
- **`Ornith is 9B, not 8B.** The user's "ornith 8b" reference is likely a casual memory of the family; the canonical base is 9B. No separate "8B" model exists in this lineage as of 2026-07-04.

**Disk budget for 3 local models:** ~38 GB raw BF16 weights + ~2 GB safetensors metadata. Plus GGUF quantizations for the spec-dec eval (each ≈ 4–6 GB compressed) and AWQ/INT4 quants (each ≈ 3 GB). With all variants on disk: ~70–80 GB. D: has 528 GB free — comfortable.

**vRAM reality:** Total resident vRAM if all three are loaded concurrently: ~38 GB BF16. Doesn't fit on a single 24 GB card. The default operational mode is **one model resident at a time**, with hot-swapping orchestrated by `pheno/model_manager.py`. Concurrent load possible only with quantization (Q4_0) — for the parallel agent sweep in `MODEL_MATRIX.md` §10, each agent loads `LFM2.5-8B-A1B-Q4_0` (~5 GB) and `Qwen3.5-0.8B-Q4_0` (always-on draft, ~1 GB).

### 1.3 Routing chain (cloud)

```
forge-dev  ── HTTP/WS ──▶  omniroute-dev  ── OpenRouter API ──▶  {ling, granite, lfm, trinity, hy3, ...}
                  ▲                                            ▲
                  │                                            │
                  └──── policy + cost cap + retry ◀──────────────┘
```

- `forge-dev` issues the agent loop and tool calls.
- `omniroute-dev` enforces: per-model cost cap, retry policy, fallback chain, response-shape normalization.
- OpenRouter is the upstream API for the 8 cloud baselines.
- Local inference (3 self-hosted) is also reachable through `omniroute-dev` once `pheno-serve-dev` is up — the router treats it as a 9th model.

## 2. March-2026 recency rule

Added as **Rule #6** to ADR 0004. Full text in §6 of that document.

Quick summary:

1. **Default cutoff:** `HF last_modified >= 2026-03-01 UTC`. Below that = `recency_dlq` by default.
2. **OR mirror exception:** if HF repo is fresh (≥ 2026-03-01) but OR `created` is pre-March, the model passes. The OR mirror is treated as a metadata view of the canonical HF weights.
3. **Stale-both:** both pre-March AND not recently updated → `recency_dlq` + needs explicit user keep/drop with a deep-justification block.
4. **Weekly re-scrape** regenerates the shortlist. Each entry has a `recency` field with a reason string. Reviewers read it; the field is required in the JSON.

## 3. HF_TOKEN handling (security policy)

Per `RISKS.md` §2 (secret leakage), the HF token provided in chat on 2026-07-04 is handled as follows:

1. **Never stored on disk.** No file in `pheno-harness/` contains the token. Confirmed by grep.
2. **Never logged.** The wrapper script `state/_round4_run.ps1` accepts the token as `args[0]`, sets `$env:HF_TOKEN` for the child Python process only, and immediately clears it after the process exits.
3. **Never committed.** `.gitignore` will be updated to exclude `state/hf_scrape/*/secrets.*` even though no such file exists yet.
4. **Rotated by user.** The token is the user's; rotation policy is the user's call. Forge does not rotate.
5. **Scope.** Token used for `HfApi.list_models` + `HfApi.model_info` reads. No write/push operations invoked.

## 4. Eval suite integration (per user 2026-07-04)

User preference: **DeepSWE + Terminal-Bench 2.0 + Terminal-Bench 2.1 + custom long-horizon** as the primary eval suites. **SWE-bench Verified is NOT preferred** and downgraded to optional regression-only.

Suite priority:

1. **`deepswe` (PRIMARY)** — 113 tasks, datacurve-ai/deep-swe. Long-horizon software engineering, separate verifier (v1.1 spec), Pier ≥ 0.3.0, `--env modal` for parallel sandboxes on cloud route.
2. **`tbench_20` (PRIMARY)** — 89 tasks, Harbor TB 2.0.
3. **`tbench_21` (PRIMARY)** — TB 2.1 (improved subset, post-2026-06, inspired by Z.ai's TB 2.0 Verified).
4. **`long_horizon` (PRIMARY)** — custom multi-step/multi-day Harbor-compatible suite derived from real agent traces (Claude, Codex, ForgeCode, Factory Droid, Cursor). See `docs/specs/002-trace-evalset.md`.
5. **`tbench_3_watch` (OPT-IN MONTHLY)** — TB 3.x compat smoke.
6. **`swebench_verified` (REGRESSION-ONLY)** — 200-task frozen subset, nightly. NOT a primary ranking signal; serves only as a regression gate so we know if a change breaks known-good behaviors.
7. **`swebench_lite` (REMOVED)** — was a candidate; not in scope.

The implementation plan (§11 in `004-implementation-plan.md`) reorders the staged PRs so **DeepSWE lifts to Stage 2** (right after TB 2.0 honest baseline), and SWE-bench Verified moves to optional regression-only (Stage 8, opt-in).

## 5. Spec-dec zoo (added to matrix spec)

The matrix spec (`docs/specs/003-model-engine-matrix.md`) §7 now covers the spec-dec frontier:

- **EAGLE-2 / EAGLE-3** — vanilla self-speculative (vanilla & lookahead).
- **Medusa** — head-based parallel candidates.
- **PLD** — prompt lookup, draft-from-prompt.
- **Lookahead decoding** — Jacobi-iteration based.
- **MTP** — multi-token prediction trained-in. Live on `protoLabsAI/Ornith-1.0-9B-MTP-GGUF`.
- **DSpark** — diffusion-based spec-dec (per user 2026-07-04: "dspark is a dflash-like diffusion speculative decoder").
- **JetSpec** — jet-iteration spec-dec (per user).
- **DDTree** — diffusion-decision-tree spec-dec (per user).
- **Speculative-speculative** — "intentional double type, speculating all possible options rather than just 1 for a given token" (per user).

Engines covered: SGLang (EAGLE, MTP, lookahead), vLLM (EAGLE, Medusa, lookahead, suffix-decoding, n-gram), TensorRT-LLM (EAGLE, MTP), llama.cpp (MTP-GGUF, PLD, lookahead).

Pheno-harness picks **SGLang primary** for the EAGLE/MTP/Lookahead path. vLLM secondary for Medusa/PLD/cross-check. llama.cpp for the MTP-GGUF Ornith derivative (where SGLang/vLLM do not yet have native MTP support).

## 6. Cost projection (per user 2026-07-04)

Per-run cost projections are in `state/hf_scrape/2026-07-04/cost_projection.md` (full model × suite × n_attempts table). Quick numbers:

- **Cloud TB 2.0 smoke (89 tasks × 1 attempt):** ~$0.5 per model for Ling ($0.01/$0.03 OR); ~$3 per model for Hy3 preview ($0.063/$0.21). Total smoke (7 models): **~$14**.
- **Cloud DeepSWE smoke (113 tasks × 1 attempt):** ~$0.7 (Ling) to ~$5 (Hy3) per model. Total smoke (7 models): **~$20**.
- **Cloud long-horizon smoke (16 tasks × 1 attempt):** ~$0.5 (Ling) to ~$3 (Hy3) per model. Total: **~$12**.
- **Full weekly sweep (TB 2.0 + DeepSWE + long-horizon × 3 attempts):** **~$200–$400** across the 7 cloud models (median $300).
- **Self-hosted sweeps are ~$0 in API cost** but consume electricity + GPU time; tracked separately under `perf_resource`.

The projection table includes token-budget assumptions, n_attempts sensitivity, and a worst-case ceiling ($900/week if every cloud model is run at max token budget and 5 attempts).

## 7. b16 (BitNet b1.58) — NOT in scope

The user noted that **b16 was never under consideration** and that I should have known this from corpus. Confirmed: b16/BitNet b1.58 does NOT appear in any of the locked picks (the TernaryBit path requires custom kernels that don't ship with SGLang 0.5.2 / vLLM 0.20.0, and the brief's 0.8B floor is well-served by `Qwen3.5-0.8B`). The 3090 Ti's VRAM is more efficiently used by BF16/AWQ-INT4 than by ternary quantization for our tier targets.

This is documented here so a future agent does not re-raise the BitNet question.

## 8. Decisions still pending user sign-off

1. **`Qwen/Qwen3.5-0.8B` text-only variant** — verify `text-generation` sibling exists, or use the multimodal variant as-is.
2. **Disk partition for `state/model_cache/`** — confirm D: (528 GB free) or move to E: (NVMe, 1.36 TB free).
3. **Sequencing: which model gets downloaded first** — recommendation: T2 workhorse `LiquidAI/LFM2.5-8B-A1B` (just-released 2026-07-02, most critical for the parallel-agent sweep), then T0/T1 dual-role `Qwen/Qwen3.5-0.8B`, then T3 mid-moe `deepreinforce-ai/Ornith-1.0-9B` + its MTP-GGUF derivative.

